  <main>
    <h1>SSCC Pilot Project</h1>
    <p>The <strong>SolarSpace Carbon Cycle (SSCC)</strong> pilot demonstrates decentralized synthesis of green ammonia (NH₃) with CO₂ capture & utilization.</p>

    <section class="card" style="margin-top:16px">
      <h2>Key Objectives</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Develop a <strong>2 kW</strong> pilot unit producing <strong>~1.5 kg NH₃/day</strong>.</li>
        <li>Reach energy efficiency <strong>&gt; 80 %</strong>.</li>
        <li>CO₂ capture efficiency <strong>&gt; 90 %</strong>.</li>
        <li>Integration with PV or hybrid renewable systems.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="card" style="margin-top:16px">
      <h2>Concept Summary</h2>
      <p>Solar power → electricity → water electrolysis (H₂). Hydrogen reacts with nitrogen (N₂) in a controlled loop to synthesize ammonia (NH₃),
         enabling compact energy storage and supporting CCU pathways.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="card" style="margin-top:16px">
